title: Lead Backend Developer
description: Returning to unicode, I worked mostly in the backend to automate the adoption process, working with social media sites, mailing systems, manual approvals, and badge processing.

title: Technical Lead
description: In the Beginning of my sophomore year, I was promoted to tech lead, where I oversee a team of developers to design and produce features on a semesterly basis, such as a part review system where users can mark up pdfs!

title: Software Developer Intern
description: During my first internship with Unicode, I worked on renewing the adopt a character site with integrations for payment processing as well as external donor databases. Go Adopt a Character!

title: Senior Camp Counselor
description: As a camp counselor, I enjoyed working with a wide range of ages and interests as I ran many different specialty camps and overnight excursions. I earned rookie counselor of the year for these efforts.

title: Began Attending Northeastern
description: In september of 2023 I began my journey at northeastern, which will take 5 years and 3 co-ops.

title: Coach / Photographer / Secretary
description: After 4 acl tears in my left knee, I decided to move to an advisory role on the club ski team, where I use my skiing, organizational, and photgraphy skills to continue helping the team.

title: Fundies 1 TA
description: For my first TA job, I went back to the basics with the fundamentals of computer science 1 accelerated section, where I helped students by facilitating office hours, running labs, and providing feedback.

title: Fundies 2 TA
description: Following the bonds made with students from my previous semester TAing, I continued my journy in the accel section of fundies 2.

title: Graduation
description: I graduated Gould Academy as salutatorian, putting an official end to my 12 year competative alpine ski racing career.

title: Software Developer
description: During the second semester of my freshmen year, I joined NER as a software developer, working on backend and frontend tickets for our websites home page.

title: Coding Coach and Brand Ambassador
description: Taught children ages 7-13 a variety of programming languages and skills including python, java, scratch, and robotics. Additionally represented brand at marketing events by recruiting potential new members.

title: Computer Science Club Co-Founder
description: During my senior year I co-founded the gould computer science club where we taught students basic programming and robotics skills.

title: Bill Taylor Essay Contest Winner
description: In my essay 'Assessing Internet Inequality in the US', I analyzed the effects of internet inequality and argued for regulations and legislation that could help this pressing issue. Read more here.

title: Scholarship Chair
description: Having been a brother for over a year, I was elected as the scholarship chair to oversee and ensure academic excellence throughout our fraternity. I am also leading the development of our custom NextJS website!

title: Head of Web Development
description: After working as a tech lead for a year, I was promoted to the head of web development, where I manage all development and technical operation of our custom project management site. I lead a team of 8 tech leads and 60+ developers to produce new features every semester!
